Q_DESC:
An expression contains only digits(1-9) and operators("+", "-", "*"). You have given this expression and value of the expression after removing all operators from it. Can you find given value by using operators(use only "+", "-", "*"). You are allowed to put any operator between any two digits,but order of digits should not change. If it is possible then print "YES"(without quotes),otherwise print "NO"(without quotes).

Input:
First line contains one integer T denoting the number of test cases.
Second line contains two space-separated integers N denoting total digits used in expression and V denoting value of expression.
Third line contains N space-separated integers denoting the digits in expression.
Output format:
For each test case print the required output in separate line..
